01:10:37.567 --> 01:10:39.277
<i>I mean, look at the cafeteria.</i>

01:10:39.360 --> 01:10:42.906
<i>Look at the food</i>
<i>that we're being told is healthy.</i>

01:10:44.074 --> 01:10:45.491
<i>They see the same thing for lunch,</i>

01:10:45.575 --> 01:10:47.953
<i>hot dogs, meatballs, and bread.</i>

01:10:48.036 --> 01:10:50.164
<i>It's day after day.</i>

01:10:50.246 --> 01:10:52.457
<i>I feel as though we have a responsibility</i>

01:10:52.540 --> 01:10:56.252
<i>to feed them way more</i>
<i>micronutrient-rich foods.</i>

01:10:56.335 --> 01:10:58.172
Why can't we offer a salad bar?

01:11:00.298 --> 01:11:02.050
<i>But kids are with us eight hours a day,</i>

01:11:02.134 --> 01:11:04.552
<i>and who's teaching them these things?</i>

01:11:04.635 --> 01:11:07.388
A lot of the parents don't know the facts,

01:11:07.472 --> 01:11:08.556
<i>and that's not their fault.</i>

01:11:08.639 --> 01:11:10.976
<i>It's just the way a lot of us were raised.</i>
<i>It was the way I was raised.</i>

01:11:11.059 --> 01:11:13.394
<i>I had no idea until I was in my 20s.</i>

01:11:17.983 --> 01:11:20.944
<i>So, I wish that there would be a buy-in</i>

01:11:21.028 --> 01:11:23.906
<i>where, you know, a district would say,</i>
<i>"This is important.</i>

01:11:23.989 --> 01:11:27.159
<i>"It's part of a balanced</i>
<i>and holistic education</i>

01:11:27.242 --> 01:11:29.619
<i>where you have academics, health."</i>

01:11:29.702 --> 01:11:34.415
<i>I mean, there really should be</i>
<i>a little something for everything.</i>

01:11:34.499 --> 01:11:39.545
There's ways to integrate in
really great, new, modern topics

01:11:39.629 --> 01:11:42.715
that they need to know
to be productive people in society.

01:11:42.800 --> 01:11:46.719
And nutrition is, as far
as I'm concerned, on top of that list.

01:11:50.598 --> 01:11:53.309
It takes more than just school.

01:11:53.392 --> 01:11:55.270
It takes a whole curriculum
built around it.

01:11:55.353 --> 01:11:57.022
<i>It takes a teacher who knows how to do it.</i>

01:11:57.105 --> 01:11:59.690
It takes time within the school day.

01:11:59.774 --> 01:12:02.820
It takes a lunchroom that's committed
to incorporating the food.

01:12:02.903 --> 01:12:04.029
<i>It takes district-wide support.</i>

01:12:04.112 --> 01:12:06.990
It takes, like, a village
to make that work.

01:12:07.074 --> 01:12:10.160
The pendulum has swung so far

01:12:10.244 --> 01:12:15.833
from eating wholesome food
to eating processed... junk

01:12:15.916 --> 01:12:18.293
in such a short amount of time

01:12:18.376 --> 01:12:22.380
with such momentum
and such power behind it

01:12:22.463 --> 01:12:27.302
that to swing it around
is really gonna take everybody.

01:12:27.385 --> 01:12:29.179
Like, all the people.

01:12:29.263 --> 01:12:31.056
And schools...

01:12:32.765 --> 01:12:35.518
The public schools,
a lot of them are not at that point.

01:12:35.601 --> 01:12:39.064
[Cross] <i>From what I've seen,</i>
<i>I can understand Eliza's frustration.</i>

01:12:39.147 --> 01:12:43.568
<i>She's right.</i>
<i>Most public schools have a long way to go.</i>

01:12:43.651 --> 01:12:47.405
<i>But then, I heard</i>
<i>about a little ray of sunshine.</i>

01:12:47.488 --> 01:12:52.535
<i>Someplace where Eliza</i>
<i>and Kate's hopes and dreams are a reality.</i>

01:12:54.913 --> 01:12:56.747
[Adin]
<i>At Ocean Knoll,</i>

01:12:56.831 --> 01:13:00.626
<i>we have more than five wellness activities</i>
<i>to keep our students going.</i>

01:13:00.710 --> 01:13:02.503
<i>Let's check these out.</i>

01:13:08.176 --> 01:13:10.220
<i>First up, the garden project.</i>

01:13:11.263 --> 01:13:13.472
<i>Miss Bond wanted us to make a movie</i>

01:13:13.556 --> 01:13:16.018
<i>about all of the health</i>
<i>and wellness at school.</i>

01:13:16.101 --> 01:13:19.437
So we got a list of everything
that we do at Ocean Knoll,

01:13:19.520 --> 01:13:21.439
<i>the yoga, this farm,</i>

01:13:21.522 --> 01:13:23.358
<i>the nutrition lab, the garden,</i>

01:13:23.441 --> 01:13:25.651
<i>after and before-school activities.</i>

01:13:25.735 --> 01:13:30.740
And then we put it together into a movie
showing how amazing

01:13:30.823 --> 01:13:33.451
the health and wellness
at Ocean Knoll really is.

01:13:36.997 --> 01:13:39.540
[Tim Baird] Joe, welcome
to Encinitas Union School District.

01:13:39.624 --> 01:13:41.209
We're here at Ocean Knoll School,

01:13:41.293 --> 01:13:42.793
and this is a pretty special place.

01:13:42.877 --> 01:13:46.589
So, what makes this school different, Tim,

01:13:46.672 --> 01:13:48.841
from other schools across America?

01:13:48.926 --> 01:13:51.386
I think we look
at more a holistic view of learning.

01:13:51.469 --> 01:13:54.722
You know, we believe
hat we're teaching to the whole child,

01:13:54.805 --> 01:13:57.808
so we do spend a lot of time in academics,

01:13:57.892 --> 01:13:59.477
and our kids do very well there.

01:13:59.560 --> 01:14:02.563
But health and wellness
is also a big part of what we teach.

01:14:02.647 --> 01:14:05.524
<i>All of our schools have</i>
<i>these amazing teaching gardens.</i>

01:14:05.608 --> 01:14:08.028
<i>But then they also study math.</i>
<i>They study science,</i>

01:14:08.111 --> 01:14:10.238
and then that connects to in the kitchen.

01:14:10.322 --> 01:14:12.115
This is not the norm,
what we're dealing with here.

01:14:12.199 --> 01:14:13.449
This is not the norm.

01:14:13.532 --> 01:14:14.784
We hope that it will become the norm.

01:14:19.664 --> 01:14:21.749
<i>Coming here really helped</i>

01:14:21.832 --> 01:14:25.337
to re-engage my passion
for working with children

01:14:25.420 --> 01:14:29.924
where, of course, the reading, and math,
and the academics are important,

01:14:30.008 --> 01:14:31.884
but really looking at the whole child,

01:14:31.969 --> 01:14:34.512
and what are we doing to produce students

01:14:34.595 --> 01:14:38.641
who are going to be successful
and happy citizens

01:14:38.724 --> 01:14:39.642
when they leave us

01:14:39.725 --> 01:14:41.644
and go out into the real world
on their own.

01:14:41.727 --> 01:14:45.731
This morning,
we're gonna make some herb pesto.

01:14:45.815 --> 01:14:48.193
Like-- [chuckles] Like always,

01:14:48.276 --> 01:14:51.154
the herbs are up to you
what you guys wanna put in.

01:14:51.238 --> 01:14:53.156
So, we have some basil

01:14:53.240 --> 01:14:55.450
and some parsley
that's looking really beautiful.

01:14:55.533 --> 01:14:57.910
If you wanna put spinach in, chard.

01:14:57.995 --> 01:15:00.330
[Jennifer Bond]
<i>Besides their regular, academic classes,</i>

01:15:00.414 --> 01:15:04.917
they have the opportunity
to be in the gardening classes.

01:15:05.002 --> 01:15:09.672
So they're hands-on,
outside of the classroom, in the garden

01:15:09.755 --> 01:15:13.592
actually experiencing what they talk about
maybe in a science lesson

01:15:13.676 --> 01:15:16.179
there, then in the garden, living it.

01:15:17.222 --> 01:15:18.597
Okay, here's a piece.

01:15:21.976 --> 01:15:24.229
That is so cool. Watch it drop in.

01:15:26.189 --> 01:15:28.108
[Christa Holder]
<i>Our kids love vegetables.</i>

01:15:28.191 --> 01:15:29.775
<i>A lot of parents thank me,</i>

01:15:29.859 --> 01:15:33.196
because their kids are willing to eat
a lot of green things

01:15:33.280 --> 01:15:34.822
that before, they never would.

01:15:34.905 --> 01:15:36.532
Oh, here's one.

01:15:36.615 --> 01:15:38.951
<i>[Holder] If they can take it </i>
<i>off of the plant and just hold it,</i>

01:15:39.036 --> 01:15:42.788
<i>there's something</i>
<i>about the engagement and the contact.</i>

01:15:42.872 --> 01:15:45.666
<i>I don't know, like...</i>
<i>The whole sensual experience.</i>

01:15:45.750 --> 01:15:47.668
<i>It's something that smells fantastic.</i>

01:15:47.752 --> 01:15:50.629
<i>Like, the colors are really engaging.</i>

01:15:50.713 --> 01:15:53.050
They want to be a part of it.

01:15:53.133 --> 01:15:54.592
How's it coming?

01:15:54.675 --> 01:15:57.720
Can we break that off,
or do I need to get a tool?

01:15:57.803 --> 01:15:59.181
-[Kids] Tool
-Tool.

01:15:59.264 --> 01:16:01.183
[Baird]
<i>I think kids love getting out in the dirt.</i>

01:16:01.266 --> 01:16:03.226
<i>You know, it's part of being a kid, </i>
<i>first of all.</i>

01:16:03.310 --> 01:16:06.438
<i>But they also enjoy,</i>
<i>I think, connecting with nature.</i>

01:16:06.521 --> 01:16:08.148
<i>What's amazing about being out here</i>

01:16:08.231 --> 01:16:10.233
<i>is they actually can see</i>
<i>where their food comes from.</i>

01:16:10.317 --> 01:16:14.071
<i>And you will see kids</i>
<i>who have harvested their produce,</i>

01:16:14.154 --> 01:16:17.282
<i>and they will...</i>
<i>They will try it. They will taste it.</i>

01:16:17.365 --> 01:16:20.077
<i>They will say, "I've never known</i>
<i>spinach tastes this good."</i>

01:16:23.621 --> 01:16:25.873
[Bond] <i> You ask any of the students</i>
<i>what their favorite class is,</i>

01:16:25.956 --> 01:16:27.625
<i>and it's the nutrition class for sure.</i>

01:16:27.708 --> 01:16:30.586
They love to be able
to cook and then eat it.

01:16:30.669 --> 01:16:34.006
[Student]
<i>We had cauliflower with pesto sauce.</i>

01:16:34.091 --> 01:16:36.301
<i>We had a garden salad,</i>

01:16:36.384 --> 01:16:40.054
<i>which was just like</i>
<i>a bunch of different plants, herbs.</i>

01:16:40.138 --> 01:16:43.015
And it's really cool,
because we get to make it ourselves.

01:16:43.100 --> 01:16:45.810
[Erin Buston]
<i>I didn't realize how unique we are.</i>

01:16:45.893 --> 01:16:49.481
But now, being exposed to
a different district that my son goes to,

01:16:49.564 --> 01:16:52.817
I got this list of foods you can't eat.

01:16:52.900 --> 01:16:55.403
All this no, no, no, no, no.

01:16:55.487 --> 01:16:57.572
And honestly, I was so shocked by it,

01:16:57.655 --> 01:17:00.283
<i>I said to their teacher,</i>
<i>"I can't believe this."</i>

01:17:00.367 --> 01:17:02.494
And she said,
"You don't have a wellness program?"

01:17:02.577 --> 01:17:05.079
<i>And I went, "Oh, no." </i> [laughs]

01:17:05.163 --> 01:17:06.664
"This is not a wellness program.

01:17:06.747 --> 01:17:10.544
These things you can't eat,
that's not a wellness program."

01:17:10.626 --> 01:17:13.087
<i>And then I thought of Encinitas,</i>
<i>and this is what we do.</i>

01:17:13.171 --> 01:17:14.755
<i>They say, "How can we be well?"</i>

01:17:14.839 --> 01:17:17.925
<i>And they focus</i>
<i>on all the good things we can do.</i>

01:17:18.008 --> 01:17:20.052
And we put the resources
in the kids' hands

01:17:20.137 --> 01:17:21.971
and let them make their choices,

01:17:22.054 --> 01:17:24.849
and it's just so much more powerful
and so much more fun.

01:17:24.932 --> 01:17:25.975
It's really fun.

01:17:28.727 --> 01:17:30.397
[Baird]
This was a dumping ground.

01:17:30.480 --> 01:17:32.357
I will tell you. It was a vacant lot.

01:17:32.440 --> 01:17:34.066
It's always been owned
by the school district.

01:17:34.151 --> 01:17:36.068
But it was full of trash.

01:17:36.153 --> 01:17:38.863
People would drop off old beds and things,

01:17:38.946 --> 01:17:40.198
so we would have to clean up.

01:17:40.282 --> 01:17:41.699
And it was really an eyesore.

01:17:41.782 --> 01:17:44.327
<i>We now... We have grown a food forest.</i>

01:17:44.411 --> 01:17:45.953
These are our fruit trees.

01:17:46.036 --> 01:17:47.205
I can see some apple here.

01:17:47.289 --> 01:17:51.125
You've got all that swiss chard.
You got your strawberries, sweet potato.

01:17:51.209 --> 01:17:55.213
This will pay for itself, really,
in the produce that we are using

01:17:55.297 --> 01:17:57.591
<i>for the teaching kitchen</i>
<i>that we have on this campus,</i>

01:17:57.673 --> 01:18:00.635
<i>and then we also have a daily salad bar</i>

01:18:00.718 --> 01:18:03.263
<i>that has fresh, locally-grown produce.</i>

01:18:03.346 --> 01:18:05.390
<i>We also give to local food banks.</i>

01:18:05.473 --> 01:18:08.017
<i>We believe the community</i>
<i>is a major part of what we do here.</i>

01:18:08.100 --> 01:18:10.520
This is one of the ways
that we can give back to our community.

01:18:10.604 --> 01:18:13.063
Tim, how many schools in America
have signs saying,

01:18:13.147 --> 01:18:14.316
"Keep your worms happy."

01:18:14.399 --> 01:18:15.525
Probably not that many.

01:18:15.609 --> 01:18:17.569
I like that you've got that here.
Now, where are the worms?

01:18:17.652 --> 01:18:19.446
-We've got worms right over here.
-I love worms.

01:18:19.529 --> 01:18:21.030
Oh, wow! Look at that.

01:18:21.113 --> 01:18:23.157
We have a lot of worms
doing their job in here.

01:18:23.241 --> 01:18:24.992
There's a whole bunch of them.
Just look at that.

01:18:25.075 --> 01:18:28.455
-[Baird] We've got some happy worms here.
-[Cross] Very happy worms.

01:18:28.538 --> 01:18:30.915
[Adin]
<i>Worms are awesome. Without worms,</i>

01:18:30.998 --> 01:18:34.877
<i>many of the plants on the farm wouldn't be</i>
<i>nearly as healthy as they are now.</i>

01:18:34.960 --> 01:18:38.130
And worms are pretty cool,
wiggling around, doing their thing.

01:18:38.215 --> 01:18:40.007
So, I think worms are cool.

01:18:42.927 --> 01:18:45.347
[Baird] <i>We have to look </i>
<i>at things differently as educators</i>

01:18:45.430 --> 01:18:46.931
<i>as to how we get at this.</i>

01:18:47.014 --> 01:18:48.974
Everybody comes back
to academics in the school district.

01:18:49.058 --> 01:18:51.394
<i>Our kids do very, very well academically.</i>

01:18:51.478 --> 01:18:54.231
Seven of our nine schools
were California Distinguished Schools.

01:18:54.314 --> 01:18:55.607
So on that side of it,

01:18:55.690 --> 01:18:57.107
I feel like the time spent

01:18:57.191 --> 01:18:59.486
on the health, and nutrition,
and the wellness

01:18:59.569 --> 01:19:00.986
has been time well spent.

01:19:01.070 --> 01:19:02.947
[guitar playing upbeat tune]

01:19:05.783 --> 01:19:08.662
[Baird] <i>But we also see</i>
<i>that our kids are healthier,</i>

01:19:08.744 --> 01:19:11.080
<i>our kids perform better</i>
<i>on state assessments</i>

01:19:11.163 --> 01:19:14.668
<i>related to strength, conditioning, </i>
<i>and flexibility. </i>

01:19:14.750 --> 01:19:16.961
<i>I think partially because of the yoga.</i>

01:19:17.044 --> 01:19:20.590
<i>Our students leave this district</i>
<i>literate in nutrition,</i>

01:19:20.674 --> 01:19:22.467
<i>literate in health and wellness,</i>

01:19:22.550 --> 01:19:25.219
and I think that's a literacy they need
as much as reading and math.

01:19:26.762 --> 01:19:31.685
Everybody at Ocean Knoll
is proud to plant something,

01:19:31.767 --> 01:19:34.562
watch it grow, help it grow,

01:19:34.646 --> 01:19:36.314
and then eat it.

01:19:36.398 --> 01:19:40.901
Eating something that you created
is just an amazing thing to do.

01:19:40.985 --> 01:19:45.155
[Baird]
<i>I think this has been, um, really synergy</i>

01:19:45.239 --> 01:19:47.575
<i>from our community, from our staff,</i>

01:19:47.659 --> 01:19:50.620
<i>from our teachers, and parents.</i>

01:19:50.704 --> 01:19:53.205
<i>And it started with some school gardens,</i>

01:19:53.290 --> 01:19:55.292
<i>and we realized that</i>
<i>within our school gardens,</i>

01:19:55.375 --> 01:19:57.711
<i>there were some amazing</i>
<i>learning opportunities happening.</i>

01:19:57.793 --> 01:19:59.379
Now, we do have some advantages.

01:19:59.462 --> 01:20:01.715
We have a year-round growing season
here in San Diego.

01:20:01.797 --> 01:20:04.634
But there are some things
that we do that any school can do.

01:20:05.801 --> 01:20:06.844
[Cross]
<i>Tim's right.</i>

01:20:06.927 --> 01:20:08.305
<i>Not everywhere has the luxury</i>

01:20:08.388 --> 01:20:11.391
<i>of the gorgeous weather</i>
<i>that is southern California.</i>

01:20:11.474 --> 01:20:16.730
<i>But weather alone doesn't determine </i>
<i>how successful a wellness program can be.</i>

01:20:16.812 --> 01:20:18.315
<i>As we've just seen,</i>

01:20:18.398 --> 01:20:21.817
<i>schools can be an awesome location</i>
<i>for a garden or farm.</i>

01:20:21.900 --> 01:20:24.571
<i>But really, the magic of these gardens</i>

01:20:24.654 --> 01:20:29.158
<i>is the way they can bring</i>
<i>a community together.</i>

01:20:29.241 --> 01:20:32.161
<i>Take Eliza's program</i>
<i>on the South Side of Chicago,</i>

01:20:32.244 --> 01:20:34.038
<i>the Windy City Harvest Farm.</i>

01:20:34.121 --> 01:20:36.957
<i>Located in one</i>
<i>of the roughest neighborhoods in the city,</i>

01:20:37.041 --> 01:20:41.463
<i>the farm stand sells fresh food</i>
<i>to the whole community at reduced rates,</i>

01:20:41.546 --> 01:20:46.343
<i>and the kids can take home</i>
<i>as much free produce as they can carry.</i>

01:20:46.426 --> 01:20:48.135
<i>The farm itself is a safe place.</i>

01:20:48.218 --> 01:20:49.763
-Here. You wanna carry it together?
-I got it.

01:20:49.845 --> 01:20:50.846
-Are you sure?
-Yeah.

01:20:50.929 --> 01:20:52.474
All right. Thank you.

01:20:52.557 --> 01:20:55.518
[Cross] <i>Where local kids can work</i>
<i>throughout the growing season</i>

01:20:55.602 --> 01:20:57.395
<i>instead of taking fast food jobs.</i>

01:20:57.479 --> 01:20:59.647
<i>It's a place </i>
<i>where they can earn a few dollars</i>

01:20:59.731 --> 01:21:02.484
<i>and maybe change their lives.</i>

01:21:02.567 --> 01:21:06.111
Every season, 90 teenagers
from all around Chicago come here

01:21:06.195 --> 01:21:09.031
<i>and work on the farm with us every day.</i>

01:21:09.114 --> 01:21:11.241
<i>They're developing a relationship </i>
<i>with their food.</i>

01:21:11.325 --> 01:21:13.745
<i>They're seeing </i>
<i>how the food makes them feel</i>

01:21:13.828 --> 01:21:15.663
<i>when they're eating in a healthy way.</i>

01:21:15.747 --> 01:21:17.499
[Student]
<i>I used to eat a bunch of French fries,</i>

01:21:17.582 --> 01:21:19.333
<i>and spicy chicken sandwiches, and stuff.</i>

01:21:19.417 --> 01:21:24.714
<i>I think the food really affected me, like,</i>
<i>emotionally and my acne.</i>

01:21:24.798 --> 01:21:26.800
<i>And I think that's </i>
<i>when it just dawned up on me</i>

01:21:26.882 --> 01:21:28.510
to start eating
more fruits and vegetables.

01:21:28.593 --> 01:21:29.677
There's so many benefits.

01:21:29.761 --> 01:21:33.055
[Fournier] <i>They're exposing themselves</i>
<i>to new opportunities,</i>

01:21:33.138 --> 01:21:37.059
and it's having a real ripple effect
throughout their whole community.

01:21:37.142 --> 01:21:38.478
Okay, how many boxes is that?

01:21:38.561 --> 01:21:39.479
-Ten.
-Ten?

01:21:39.562 --> 01:21:40.647
[Fournier]
<i>These are teenagers,</i>

01:21:40.730 --> 01:21:43.107
<i>but it's never too young to start,</i>

01:21:43.190 --> 01:21:47.027
<i>and it's never too old to start,</i>
<i>and that's what we're seeing.</i>

01:21:47.111 --> 01:21:50.072
<i>They're eating healthy,</i>
<i>taking food home to their family,</i>

01:21:50.155 --> 01:21:53.660
<i>moving their bodies 20 hours a week</i>
<i>for seven weeks.</i>

01:21:54.619 --> 01:21:56.538
That's how habits are created.

01:21:56.621 --> 01:21:59.457
In my opinion, if you get the kids,
everybody else is gonna follow.

01:21:59.541 --> 01:22:01.668
'Cause kids don't wanna be sick
like their parents.

01:22:01.751 --> 01:22:04.128
And a lot of times,
parents still won't do the right thing,

01:22:04.211 --> 01:22:06.922
because they think
their kids are not gonna like it.

01:22:07.005 --> 01:22:08.633
[Fournier]
<i>Even if you think you won't like it,</i>

01:22:08.716 --> 01:22:11.260
<i>take a risk. Try it.</i>

01:22:11.343 --> 01:22:14.764
<i>You might have discovered</i>
<i>your most favorite food in the world.</i>

01:22:14.848 --> 01:22:16.599
Y'all got me hooked.

01:22:16.683 --> 01:22:20.770
And that lesson carries on
through every other aspect of their life,

01:22:20.854 --> 01:22:22.104
not just with food.

01:22:22.187 --> 01:22:24.566
Take a risk. Try it.

01:22:24.649 --> 01:22:26.024
You might like it.

01:22:26.108 --> 01:22:27.943
Being able to have a voice

01:22:28.026 --> 01:22:31.405
to educate people about taking control
of your health, like you said,

01:22:31.489 --> 01:22:33.783
is just the most powerful thing
one can do.

01:22:38.663 --> 01:22:41.081
Emily Dickinson once said,

01:22:41.165 --> 01:22:43.292
"If you take care of the small things,

01:22:43.375 --> 01:22:46.211
the big things take care of themselves."

01:22:46.295 --> 01:22:47.963
As we've just seen,

01:22:48.046 --> 01:22:52.217
it's gonna take a lot of small steps
to tackle childhood obesity

01:22:52.301 --> 01:22:56.263
<i>and ensure that our kids</i>
<i>have a longer, healthier life.</i>

01:22:57.474 --> 01:22:59.433
<i>From smart swaps,</i>

01:22:59.517 --> 01:23:01.310
<i>to starting a garden,</i>

01:23:01.393 --> 01:23:02.978
<i>to reading labels,</i>

01:23:03.061 --> 01:23:05.732
<i>to learning how to cook,</i>

01:23:05.815 --> 01:23:09.234
<i>there's a lot of small things</i>
<i>that everyone can do</i>

01:23:09.318 --> 01:23:11.738
<i>to make changes in their lives</i>

01:23:11.821 --> 01:23:13.740
<i>or the lives of those around them.</i>

01:23:14.908 --> 01:23:17.911
<i>Now, no one is saying this is easy.</i>

01:23:17.993 --> 01:23:21.664
<i>With busy parents,</i>
<i>under-funded and over-stretched schools,</i>

01:23:22.749 --> 01:23:25.375
<i>lack of access and knowledge,</i>

01:23:25.459 --> 01:23:27.545
<i>there are some real hurdles to overcome.</i>

01:23:27.629 --> 01:23:31.089
<i>But there's a place</i>
<i>for all kinds of approaches,</i>

01:23:31.173 --> 01:23:35.052
<i>whether it's one educator</i>
<i>talking about sugary drinks</i>

01:23:35.135 --> 01:23:38.347
<i>or a talking carrot</i>
<i>on a nutrition mission,</i>

01:23:38.430 --> 01:23:40.975
<i>or 13-year-olds staging a boycott,</i>

01:23:41.058 --> 01:23:45.563
<i>or a whole school district putting </i>
<i>nutrition at the center of its curriculum.</i>

01:23:45.647 --> 01:23:47.481
<i>Some programs are simple.</i>

01:23:47.565 --> 01:23:49.066
<i>Others are complex.</i>

01:23:50.275 --> 01:23:52.069
<i>All make a difference.</i>

01:23:54.196 --> 01:23:55.573
<i>And let's take heart</i>

01:23:55.657 --> 01:23:59.117
<i>that most of the experts</i>
<i>I've talked to on this journey</i>

01:23:59.201 --> 01:24:02.120
<i>are actually really positive </i>
<i>about the future.</i>

01:24:02.204 --> 01:24:04.206
<i>They think we're on the right track.</i>

01:24:06.793 --> 01:24:10.755
<i>But they're all well aware</i>
<i>that we're not gonna snap our fingers</i>

01:24:10.838 --> 01:24:13.382
<i>and end childhood obesity overnight.</i>

01:24:13.465 --> 01:24:14.968
It's gonna take some time,

01:24:15.050 --> 01:24:18.888
perhaps a long time,
to change a nation's eating habits.

01:24:19.889 --> 01:24:21.306
<i>But if we can do it,</i>

01:24:21.390 --> 01:24:23.141
<i>one child at a time...</i>

01:24:25.102 --> 01:24:26.520
<i>one family at a time...</i>

01:24:28.022 --> 01:24:29.439
That's how you are with chocolate.

01:24:29.523 --> 01:24:30.984
<i>One community at a time...</i>

01:24:33.736 --> 01:24:37.740
<i>pretty soon, we might just be able</i>
<i>to tick the box on this one</i>

01:24:37.824 --> 01:24:40.200
and call it a job well done.

01:24:42.662 --> 01:24:44.706
Anybody who tells you
we're not making progress

01:24:44.789 --> 01:24:46.958
doesn't know what they're talking about.

01:24:47.041 --> 01:24:50.252
Nobody could have predicted five years ago
we'd be where we are. Nobody.

01:24:50.335 --> 01:24:55.090
And I was getting in, ready to dig in
and dedicate my life to this,

01:24:55.173 --> 01:24:56.091
and I would have told you

01:24:56.174 --> 01:24:58.135
if we would have gotten
a third of where we are,

01:24:58.218 --> 01:24:59.344
I would have been ecstatic.

01:24:59.428 --> 01:25:01.305
So, we're making huge progress.

01:25:01.388 --> 01:25:04.099
It doesn't mean there's not, you know,
decades more work to do.

01:25:04.182 --> 01:25:06.393
-That's a good-news story, isn't it?
-It's a great-news story.

01:25:06.476 --> 01:25:09.229
I actually believe that it is kids,

01:25:09.313 --> 01:25:10.648
they're gonna make their own future.

01:25:10.732 --> 01:25:12.692
They're in the mood for it. They want it.

01:25:12.775 --> 01:25:14.068
They've got the information.

01:25:14.151 --> 01:25:15.569
They're enthusiastic about it.

01:25:15.653 --> 01:25:16.821
I have a tremendous amount of hope.

01:25:17.947 --> 01:25:22.159
Everybody has the ability
to help change a school.

01:25:22.242 --> 01:25:26.413
And schools are hungry
for this kind of change.

01:25:26.496 --> 01:25:30.292
Nobody, no teacher,
no principal, no food service director,

01:25:30.375 --> 01:25:34.296
wants kids to show up at their desk
in the morning not well-nourished

01:25:34.379 --> 01:25:36.423
and not ready to learn.

01:25:36.506 --> 01:25:40.762
